  "prompt": "What are some good novels about farmers?",
  "response": "Here are some notable novels featuring farmers or agricultural life:\n\n1. \"The Good Earth\" by Pearl S. Buck\n- Classic novel about a Chinese farmer's life\n\n2. \"Of Mice and Men\" by John Steinbeck\n- Set during the Great Depression, featuring farm workers\n\n3. \"Plainsong\" by Kent Haruf\n- Story of farmers in rural Colorado\n\n4. \"Giants in the Earth\" by Ole Edvart R\u00f6lvaag\n- About Norwegian immigrants farming in the Dakota Territory\n\n5. \"A Thousand Acres\" by Jane Smiley\n- Pulitzer Prize-winning novel about a farming family in Iowa\n\n6. \"Far from the Madding Crowd\" by Thomas Hardy\n- Classic novel set in rural England with farmer characters\n\n7. \"Hannah Coulter\" by Wendell Berry\n- Part of Berry's Port William series about rural agricultural life\n\n8. \"The Grapes of Wrath\" by John Steinbeck\n- Famous novel about farmers during the Dust Bowl era\n\n9. \"Cold Sassy Tree\" by Olive Ann Burns\n- Features rural Southern farming community life\n\n10. \"Rural Free\" by Rachel Peden\n- A memoir-style novel about Midwestern farm life\n\nThese novels offer diverse perspectives on farming across different time periods and cultures.",
